frameDefinitions: An Entity ends up with a particular new Final_quality.
This frame contains nouns denoting a rank or level within an established hierarchy.
A Controlling_entity, Controlling_situation, or Controlling_variable control a Dependent_entity, Dependent_situation, or Dependent_variable.
A New filler occupies a Role or serves a Function after the Old filler ceases to occupy the position.
A Fugitive avoids recapture by or on the authority of Authorities in relation to a Crime which the Fugitive has committed or is suspected of having committed.

An Entity that has characteristics which change over time is at a point or in a phase of its development in which, compared to other actual or expected stages of development, it possesses extremely high or low powers or intensity.
frameExamples: He is in fact a <t>fugitive</t> of the law and you must inform the police if you see him.
The Tang Dynasty was the <t>high point</t> of the Silk Road's importance.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Entity</fen> which undergoes a change so that it possesses the <fen>Final_quality</fen>.
The quality that the <fen>Entity</fen> has at the end of the event.
When the change occurs.
Where the change takes place.
The Rank itself, usually denoted by the noun.
An entity which holds a particular <fen>Rank</fen>.
A thing or person whose behavior controls a <fen>Dependent_entity</fen>, <fen>Dependent_situation</fen>, or <fen>Dependent_variable</fen>.
An entity, usually a thing, that is influenced in its behavior by a <fen>Controlling_entity</fen> or an <fen>Controlling_situation</fen>.
A scalar variable (with unspecified value) which has an effect on the <fen>Dependent_entity</fen>, <fen>Dependent_situation</fen>, or <fen>Dependent_variable</fen>.
A situation whose temporal or other characteristics are influenced by a <fen>Controlling_entity</fen>, <fen>Controlling_situation</fen>, or <fen>Controlling_variable</fen>.
A scalar variable, whose value depends on the behavior of a <fen>Controlling_entity</fen>, a <fen>Controlling_situation</fen>, or a <fen>Controlling_variable</fen>.
A situation whose temporal or other characteristics control a <fen>Dependent_entity</fen>, <fen>Dependent_situation</fen>, or <fen>Dependent_variable</fen>.
The <fex name='deg'>Degree</fex> to which the Controlling element affects the Dependent element.
The <fex name='tim'>Time</fex> at which the controlling occurs.
The location at which the controlling occurs.
The new filler of the <fen>Role</fen> that was previously occupied by the <fen>Old</fen> filler.
The category that the <fen>New</fen> and <fen>Old</fen> entities fit into as a result of the <fen>Function</fen> they serve.
The (generally desirable) state of affairs that the <fen>New</fen> and <fen>Old</fen> entities are involved in bringing about.
The entity that occupied the <fen>Role</fen> or served the <fen>Function</fen> before the <fen>New</fen> filler.
The time at which the <fen>New</fen> takes up the <fen>Role</fen> previously occupied by the <fen>Old</fen>.
The <fen>Fugitive</fen> has escaped and/or is evading capture by law enforcement <fen>Authorities</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Fugitive</fen> is evading law enforcement.
This role identifies the general <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Fugitive</fen> is located.
An concrete or abstract entity that possesses characteristics that change over time.

A point or phase in time when, viewed across the actual or expected development, the <fen>Entity</fen>'s powers have reached an extreme high or low point. The point or phase is often identified metonymically by reference to a product created by the <fen>Entity</fen> or an event involving the <fen>Entity</fen>.
listRoleExamples: Move the slider on the SpeedBar while playing audio or video material to control <fex>playback speed</fex>.
The traditional thatched roof has often been replaced <fex>by corrugated galvanized iron</fex>.
What gas replaced Hydrogen <fex>as a safer medium for use in balloons</fex> on account it does not burn?
Oil and gas replaced coal <fex>in heating homes, in industry, and in transportation</fex>.
The electron was discovered and <fex>electricity</fex> replaced gas lamps.
When electricity replaced oil <fex>in the early 1930's</fex>, the steady beam was replaced by a flashing light.
Only two years earlier <fex>she</fex> had been on the lam from charges of embezzlement.
He was a fugitive <fex>in the early 1990s</fex>.
Sloan, on the lam <fex>in Michigan</fex> for the last five months, is due to appear in court this Monday.
Midway was the ZENITH <fex>of Japanese military advancements</fex>.
<fex>Watergate</fex> was the ZENITH of American investigative journalism.
